Subject: Info on LA50 switch settings.

SW1-1 thru SW1-4 define the character set.  All 4 open means U.S. ASCII.
SW1-5 is graphics aspect ratio.  Open is 144 dpi, closed is 180 dpi.
SW1-6 and SW1-7 define protocol.  Both open means to use XON/XOFF.
SW1-8 is right margin.  Open means stay at column 80, closed starts new line.
The factory setting is all SW1 switches open.

SW2-1 thru SW2-3 define the baud rate. OOO=4800, OOC=3600, OCO=2400,
  OCC=1200, COO=600, COC=300, CCO=200, CCC=110.  Fastest when all open.
SW2-4 thru SW2-6 define data bits and parity.  OCC=7O, CCC=7E, OOC=7M, COO=7S,
  OCO=8O, CCO=8E, OOO=8N (8 data bits, no parity, 1 stop bit).
SW2-6 and SW2-7 are not documented.  SW2-6 is closed and SW2-7 is open.
The factory setting is all SW2 switches open except for SW2-7.

The LA50 is usually set up for 4800 baud, 8 data bits, no parity, 1 stop bit,
XON/XOFF flow control, US ASCII character set.
